This is the equipment status of my BT II characters at writing.

This list also reflects the order of my characters.

For some of the stages you can only take six characters, for one stage only
four, the rest of the time I keep all seven positions occupied the rest of the
time, if only to keep out the Dopplegangers.

1.      Voodoo Dreamer          ( Monk )
        1. Leather Gloves
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Mthr Helm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Mthr Shield
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Master Key
        8.

2.      Halbarad                ( Hunter )
        1. Gauntlets
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Dmnd Helm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Admt Shield
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Sword of Zar
        8. Nospen Ring                  (I think that he has it)

3.      Aragorn                 ( Hunter )
        1. Gauntlets
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Dmnd Helm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Admt Shield
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Crystal Sword
        8.

4.      Belgarath               ( Bard )
        1. Mthr Gloves
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Dmnd Helm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Admt Shield
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Flame Horn
        8.

5.      Bilbo Baggins           ( Rogue )
        1. Leather Gloves
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Admt Helm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Admt Shield
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Admt Sword
        8.

6.      Cirion                  ( Archmage )
        1. Leather Gloves
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Wizhelm
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Buckler
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Mage Staff
        8. Dragon Wand

7.      Mithrandir              ( Archmage )
        1. Leather Gloves
        2. Bracers (4)
        3. Wizhlem
        4. Elf Cloak
        5. Buckler
        6. Shield Ring
        7. Mage Staff
        8. Dragon Wand

You will see that my rogue has been put at number five (he was at number
three) this is because he has become too vulnerable because of his armour
class.  But do not be tempted to get replace him with a new, more resilient
character.  The reason I say this is because I have played Bard's Tale III
and the rogue is one of the most critical characters in the game (he
develops a critical hit ability).
